# Naming Conventions

## Vue Components
- **Component files**: PascalCase with capital first letter (`UserProfile.vue`, `Index.vue`, `Login.vue`)
- **Component names**: PascalCase (`UserProfile`, `LoginForm`, `DashboardWidget`)

## Other Files
- **Services**: kebab-case with `.service.ts` (`user.service.ts`, `report.service.ts`)
- **Stores**: kebab-case with `.store.ts` (`auth.store.ts`, `app.store.ts`)
- **Types**: kebab-case with `.types.ts` or `.d.ts` (`user.types.ts`, `app.d.ts`)
- **Utils and other modules**: descriptive kebab-case (`constants.ts`, `error-parser.ts`)

## Critical Rule: Vue Component File Names
**All Vue component files MUST start with a capital letter.**

✅ **Correct:**
- `Index.vue`
- `Login.vue` 
- `UserProfile.vue`
- `DashboardWidget.vue`

❌ **Incorrect:**
- `index.vue` (will cause production build failures)
- `login.vue` (will cause production build failures)
- `userProfile.vue` (inconsistent casing)

## Rationale
- Production builds on Linux are case-sensitive
- Development on Windows/Mac may not catch case mismatches
- Consistent casing prevents runtime import errors
- Follows Vue.js community standards